                    </expan>
                </egXML>
                <p>A monogram should be treated as an expansion of abreviation.</p>
                <p>In the diplomatic edition an hyphen (−) should separate the letters forming the monogram and, in case of a monogram with letters in the quarters,
                    a vertical bar (|) should separate the letters in the upper quarters from those in the lower quarters.</p>
                <p>See also: "<ref target="SigiDoc_form-symbolnotmean.html">Symbols</ref>" (not meaning-bearing).</p>
